==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dinar
<hw>Di"nar</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧"n⟦etil⟧r <it>or</it> d⟦esl⟧*n⟦aum⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. <ets>d⟦imac⟧n⟦amac⟧r</ets>, from Gr.
<grk>dhna`rion</grk>, fr. L. <ets>denarius</ets>. See
<er>Denier</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A petty money of accounts of
Persia; 100 <ex>dinars</ex> constituted a
<partof>rial</partof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ancient gold coin of the East, issued by various
Islamic countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the unit of currency of Yugoslavia. One dinar equals
100 paras. Abbreviated <abbr>Din.</abbr></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dinarchy</ent>⟦br⟧
